Clean build. Here's a summary of what I found and fixed:

`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`
**Why cross-origin iframe elements can't normally reach the panel:**
- `document.elementFromPoint()` returns the `<iframe>` element itself, never its cross-origin content
- `document.querySelectorAll("*")` only finds main-document elements
- The Navigator walks `el.children`, which for `<iframe>` returns its DOM children (empty), not the content document

**But there are edge cases:** the `tuner:select` custom event API accepts any Element, so external code could theoretically pass a cross-origin element. The `infer()` function already had a try/catch, but three `getComputedStyle()` call sites were unprotected.
`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`

## Summary of changes

### Already resilient (no changes needed)
- **`infer.ts:178-192`** вҖ” try/catch around `getComputedStyle` returns safe defaults (empty config, tag name, zero spacing)
- **`scope.ts:37-57`** вҖ” `getCustomProperties` has try/catch around stylesheet iteration and `el.matches()`
- **`getStableSelector` / `buildBreadcrumb`** вҖ” parent chain walks terminate safely at `null`
- **`Selector.tsx`** вҖ” `elementFromPoint()` naturally returns `<iframe>` elements, not their contents

### Fixed (3 unprotected `getComputedStyle` calls)

| File | Line | Fix |
|------|------|-----|
| `util.ts:191` | `isNavigableElement()` | Wrapped `getComputedStyle(el).display` in try/catch; returns `false` on error |
| `Overlay.tsx:149` | `isGridContainer` memo | Added try/catch; returns `false` on error |
| `Overlay.tsx:155` | `isFlexContainer` memo | Added try/catch; returns `false` on error |

### Test coverage
- New test file `crossOriginGuard.test.ts` вҖ” 9 tests covering cross-origin iframe + shadow DOM scenarios across `infer()`, `getStableSelector()`, `buildBreadcrumb()`, and `isNavigableElement()`.

